  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a Sub Inspector (SI) in the Delhi Police after graduation, you need to follow specific steps, which include meeting eligibility criteria, preparing for examinations, and undergoing the selection process. Here's a detailed outline:\n\n### Eligibility Criteria:\n1. **Educational Qualification**: You must have a bachelor's degree from a recognized university.\n2. **Age Limit**: \n   - Generally, the age limit for candidates is between 20 to 25 years. However, age relaxations may apply to reserved categories (like SC/ST/OBC).\n3. **Physical Standards**: You must meet the physical standards set by the Delhi Police. These standards include height, chest measurements, and other fitness criteria.\n4. **Nationality**: You should be a citizen of India.\n\n### Selection Process:\n1. **Notification**: Keep an eye on official notifications from the Delhi Police or the Staff Selection Commission (SSC), as the recruitment for SIs is usually conducted through SSC.\n2. **Examinations**:\n   - **Preliminary Examination**: An initial written test where candidates answer multiple-choice questions.\n   - **Main Examination**: Those who clear the preliminary exam will then have to take the main exam.\n   - **Physical Efficiency Test (PET)**: Candidates who pass the written exams will be required to undergo physical tests.\n   - **Interview**: An interview may be conducted to assess the candidates' suitability for the role.\n3. **Medical Examination**: Successful candidates in the earlier stages will need to pass a medical examination to ensure they are fit for service.\n\n### Preparation:\n1. **Syllabus Study**: Familiarize yourself with the syllabus for SSC SI recruitment, which generally includes topics related to General Knowledge, Current Affairs, Logical Reasoning, Arithmetic, and English.\n2. **Physical Training**: Begin physical training for the PET to meet the fitness standards required.\n3. **Mock Tests**: Take practice tests and previous years' question papers to enhance your preparation.\n\n### Application Process:\n1. **Online Application**: Apply online through the official website of SSC when the recruitment notification is released.\n2. **Interview/Documentation**: Keep all necessary documents ready, including educational certificates, identity proof, and any other required papers.\n\n### Final Steps:\n- Once selected, you will undergo training at the police training academy before being posted to your respective unit.\n\n### Conclusion:\nStaying updated on recruitment notifications and preparing systematically for the exams while meeting physical requirements will enhance your chances of becoming a Sub Inspector in the Delhi Police. Good luck!",
